Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.state.storeview

Class PropertyAwareEntityStoreScan<CURSOR extends StorageEntityScanCursor,​FAILURE extends Exception>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.state.storeview.PropertyAwareEntityStoreScan<CURSOR,​FAILURE>
  • Type Parameters:
    CURSOR - the type of cursor used to read the records.
    FAILURE - on failure during processing.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    StoreScan<FAILURE>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NodeStoreScan, RelationshipStoreScan
    public abstract class PropertyAwareEntityStoreScan<CURSOR extends StorageEntityScanCursor,​FAILURE extends Exception>
extends Object
implements StoreScan<FAILURE>
    Scan store with the view given by iterator created by getEntityIdIterator(). This might be a full scan of the store or a partial scan backed by LabelScanStore or RelationshipTypeScanStore. The cursor is placed on each record and then processed, this is where we extract updates for indexes that we are populating.
